<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1923-08-30T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1923-08-30T10:00:00-05:00" n="353" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d353">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">815.00/2674: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Honduras</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Morales</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tegucigalpa</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-08-30T09:00:00-06:00"><hi rend="italic">August 30,
                                        1923—9 a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received August 31—9:50
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>74. Referring to the Department’s telegram of August 28, 7 p.m. The
                            President informed me that he was willing to assure the candidates that
                            he would not impose a candidate at the forthcoming elections and would
                            do everything within his power to guarantee free elections. …</p>
                        <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Morales</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>